		<tr>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				Well first off, I just want to say to all those that don't like the change. I say how is the change any different from a naked pk running around? Meaning what do you get off a naked pk for loot? That&#8217;s right nothing, maybe some coins if he/she happens to have them (just like it is now). So really this change has just leveled the playing field UNTIL (hopefully) they find a better way to handle the problem of naked pk's. You have to acknowledge that melee types that depend on armor when fighting npc's were at a disadvantage the way it was.  <br>  <br>   So here is my proposal to keep looting in place, I came up with this idea with several others in ooc chat shortly after the server was patched correctly. And if this has been proposed before, forgive me and someone post the answer from verant if they considered this already. <br>  <br>   *IF* verant could put a value on items, then maybe they could make it where whoever loots can only loot something of equal value they have equipped(value on items determined by verant or player input possibly). Now they would have to make it where ONLY the person that does most damage can loot. That way someone naked cannot help and just let someone with full armor loot or vice versa. So if a naked pk kills another player he gains nothing cause there is nothing of comparable value equipped at the time. They would also have to make it where once you are in combat, you cannot switch items in your equipped inventory until after you have looted. Or until after a certain amount of time of being in attack mode if no one is killed(includes casting harmful spells on others even with attack mode off).They would have to set a time limit of where the person given permission to loot equals the time before they can move inventory around again. This way they cannot wait around until they can switch their inventory and then loot, to exploit that. They would just no longer have rights to loot the player. The exception possibly they could make to this is melee weapons being switched during combat, leaving melee slots non lootable still and not counting as a value item (unless some way to leave them lootable and make this non exploitable by switching weapons). Also healers would be added as damage towards the person(s) that is fighting the one they are healing. That way they would be the only person able to loot if they did most damage. Forcing the equipped value rule on them as well. If the healer is out of the pvp range (within 8 levels for TZ, VZ and 4 for Rallos) they cannot loot, as well as any other.  <br>  <br>     Well that is my proposal to keep looting in, but to do something about the cowards that run around naked, item shopping. And then they cry that the change has made the server a care bear server. Who is the care bear I ask? Yea I think you know....long as you can hide safely behind not relying on items for npc combat and prey on those that do...you are the weak and caused the change to come.  <br>  <br>   Well anyway, any that can see exploits with this idea, have something to add to it, or support the idea...please post. I have a feeling this may be too complex for verant to do....but just an idea I wanted to throw out there. <br> 		

