			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				Would it be strictly equal value because if it is you have two problems. <br> 1)A twink will be unlootable, Players who don't have items that match up to the cost of Crafted Mail or Robe of Oracle and such will not be able to loot the twink even if they kill him. <br> 2)If it is equal or less a twink would be able to loot anything from a non-twinked players corpse being as the twinked items will be worth far more. <br>  <br> As another solution you could have level restrictions on items. The restriction level could be set by the question &quot;Can a party of level XX characters without help get that item?&quot;. For example a group of level 8 characters can kill the orc trainer and get the SBS so level 8 characters can use SBS. A group of level 1 characters cannot kill an Orc Trainer(without help) so therefore they cannot use a SBS. Items above the characters level restriction are lootable regardless of how much your items are worth. 		

