				I personally think that if verant had spent a LITTLE more time on the faction system they USED to have when pking, it would work. As it is now, they implemented the faction system, I protected myself from pkers, won, and lost faction with my race. As a result, I can no longer buy from merchants in my city (except emerald warriors and Scouts of Tunare). When they removed that faction system, they should have reset previous bad faction on chars. <br>  <br> NOTE: Faction systems on pvp DO work, IF implemented properly. Take M59 for example; a player is WHITE named, indicating that he has never harmed or killed another, the option to &quot;not accidentally strike and innocent&quot; was implemented in commands. IF an innocent was accidentally hit by a WHITE named person, or attempt to pk a WHITE named person, their names became YELLOW, no longer making them an innocent, and thereby they were able to be struck by innocents and pkers alike...NOW...if a WHITE named person was killed by a YELLOW or another WHITE (namely a new pker), their name became RED, indicating to all around, that they had indeed murdered. In addition, after a certain numbers of murders were committed by said individual, a &quot;revenant&quot; would appear to avenge the innocent victims. The killer was never safe from this revenant unless indoors, and until the revenant was killed or the murderer was killed, it would hound you forever and ever, and they were usually a bit higher level than the killer. <br>  <br> I am in no way suggesting verant COPY that system, but am simply showing that a working faction system CAN BE ESTABLISHED with a few heads planning and working on making it viable. <br>  <br> *Whew* <br>  <br> Oh and btw, the person hunted down by the revenant LOST xp and was able to be looted, and if they were helped in anyway by &quot;friends&quot; those friends gained their OWN revenant. <br>  <br> I, for one, can tell you the FRUSTRATION involved in not being able to use merchants. If anything, a system like this would truly cut down on kin-slaying and make a killer THINK before he killed other races of cities he may want to buy/sell/quest from.		

