			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				I find this whole argument to be very interesting, and every viewpoint put forth has some validity in my opinion.  However, my overall opinion is that Verant has handled the pk issue very well.  The problem on the pk servers, just as in real life, is that people have their own agendas, some to roleplay, others to bring Quake to Norrath.  I think that the more &quot;invisible&quot; Verrant's influence is in this process, the better.  As it is, money and one item seems fair... it is not excessive in terms of what one stands to lose.  As for the naked pker's, I view them from a roleplaying standpoing as &quot;soul-less ones&quot; or simply &quot;the insane.&quot;  They are simply an evil we must face and be prepared for.  Also, there is nothing more gratifying that finding a known pker in his &quot;inoffensive&quot; leveling mode... where they are actually wearing armor and fighting monsters just like the rest of us... and ambushing them with a few of your close friends.  Hear them whine for a change and beg for peace... and not get it.		

